 The successful candidate has a strong background working for a SaaS, B2B tech start-up, is an organized, highly motivated, ambitious self-starter with great communication skills and analytical abilities. 
At Aera, we deliver the cognitive technology that enables the Self-Driving Enterpriseâ„¢: a Cognitive Operating Systemâ„¢ that connects you with your business and autonomously orchestrates your operations. Aera's Cognitive OS leverages the best of artificial intelligence, machine learning, natural language processing, big data, and enterprise domain expertise to deliver Cognitive Automation at scale for some of the world's largest companies. 
This will primarily work out of our SF or Mountain View office. Open to remote candidates. Must be located in the US. 
 Responsibilities 
Partner with the business leaders and support the operational and capacity planning 
Support setting up targets for the key metrics and track the actuals 
Support the assessment of resource allocation and utilization for each business function 
Work closely with the accounting team to support the month-end close process and reporting 
Support critical planning processes including long range planning, forecasting and annual budgeting 
Develop, maintain and improve financial models to support investment initiatives and â€˜what-ifâ€™ scenario planning 
